Being the wife of an army person, Parikshit and I go days without seeing each other. And most of the time due to my hectic shoots, I spend lots of time alone... it gets difficult for me to manage my work and household chores.

And while Parikshit makes sure that whenever we are together, all the household work is divided equally and that I don't have any burden with household work, this makes me realize how difficult the situation would be for those women who have to do everything single handedly. 

When two people choose to get married and share their lives, they need to share everything with each other... including the responsibility of household chores. and till everything is shared equally, it cannot be called an equal relationship. As women, we need to stand up, and speak up for ourselves. We need to demand equality. 

This amazing film by @ariel.india is bringing this conversation forward, and reminding us that as families, we need to #SeeEqual and #ShareTheLoad equally! #AD #Ariel #ArielIndia
